Defendant David J Radionov in court with attorney James Edgar Toran.  Mary Brejcha appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Case called for sentencing hearing. State presents arguments. Victims presents statements. Defense counsel presents statements. Court imposed the following sentence:

  The Defendant was sentenced to the following:

IMPOSED AND STAYED SENTENCE OF:   

 6 YEARS IMPRISONMENT  
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF INITIAL CONFINEMENT
  -  3 YEAR(S) OF EXTENDED SUPERVISION;

TERM OF PROBATION:  4 YEAR(S);

CONDITIONS OF PROBATION:  
*AODA Assessment and follow through with any treatment recommended;
*Absolute Sobriety;  Random U.A.'s ; 
*Not to possess or use any alcohol
*Follow through with any treatment and/or counseling recommended by Agent;
*Maintain employment and/or combination of schooling 
*No contact with the victim/residence
*DNA sample to be provided if not yet previously done.

RESTITUTION:  $412.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation - restitution to be paid before costs or fines);

COURT COSTS:  $268.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation); 

DNA SURCHARGE:  $250.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation);

CONDITION TIME:  12 months huber released for work and treatment, forthwidth. 8 days credit. 

IF REVOKED:
Defendant is eligible for Challenge Incarceration Program.
Defendant is eligible for Substance Abuse Program.

Felony warnings, voting rights and firearms warnings given.
